## 2. Core Features

### 2.1 Command-Line Interface

**Framework:** {% if cli_framework == 'cobra' %}Cobra (github.com/spf13/cobra){% elif cli_framework == 'urfave-cli' %}urfave/cli (github.com/urfave/cli/v2){% else %}Standard library `flag` package{% endif %}

**Architecture:** `cmd/main.go` is a thin entry point that delegates to `internal/cli.Execute()`. All argument parsing and command logic lives in `internal/cli`, which keeps it directly unit-testable without touching `os.Args` or process exit codes.

**Built-in commands:**
- `hello NAME` - example subcommand, replace with real functionality
- `--version` - print the current version
- `--verbose` / `-v` - enable verbose output{% if cli_framework == 'urfave-cli' %} (no short alias, since `-v` is reserved by urfave/cli for `--version`){% endif %}

{% if has_config_file %}
### 2.2 Configuration

**Format:** {{ config_format | upper }}

**Loading:** `internal/config.Load(path)` reads the file if present; if it does not exist, `internal/config.Default()` supplies built-in defaults. Missing files are not treated as errors.
{% endif %}

