## 4. Quality Assurance

{% if include_tests %}
### 4.1 Testing Strategy

**Framework:** standard library `testing`{% if use_testify %} + testify for assertions{% endif %}

**Approach:** `internal/cli` exposes testable entry points (`Run`/`Execute` variants that accept `io.Writer` for output) instead of writing directly to `os.Stdout`, so command behavior can be asserted without spawning a subprocess.

**Test Execution:**
```bash
go test ./...{% if test_coverage %} -cover{% endif %}
```
{% endif %}

{% if include_linting %}
### 4.2 Code Quality Standards

**Formatting:** `gofmt` (enforced via `make fmt`)
**Linting:** golangci-lint (govet, errcheck, staticcheck, unused, gofmt, goimports)
**Static Analysis:** `go vet`
{% endif %}

